<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2, img, p { margin: 0; } td { padding-top: 0 !important; } p { margin-bottom: 10px; } </mj-style>
    <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" />
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3">
    
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Logo Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/logo.png" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" alt="" />
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              margin-top:2px;
            ">Did you know the President of the United States receives a top-secret briefing on national security every morning?</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            "><strong>On 11th Jan 2025 weekend edition:</strong></p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4; 
              padding-left:10px;
            ">→ Orthodox Christmas</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left:10px;
            ">→ New Orleans resilience</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left:10px;
            ">→ California blazes</p>
          
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- THE BIG ONE-->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="2px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          padding-top:14px;
          color:#4D3060;
            text-align: left;
            letter-spacing:6px;
            border-bottom:2px solid #4D3060;
            text-transform:uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
              padding-bottom:8px;
            ">THE BIG ONE</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- THE BIG ONE contents-->
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Trump’s Greenland prospects</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-jan-11-1.png" alt="Trump’s Greenland prospects" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Donald Trump's renewed <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bo-1-interest-in-greenland" target="_blank">interest in Greenland</a> has created tension. He asserts that Greenland is crucial for U.S. national and economic security. Trump Jr.'s son visited the world’s largest island this week, raising concerns among Greenlanders and Danes. Danish Prime Minister Mette Frederiksen emphasized that <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bo-2-greenland-determines-its-fate" target="_blank">Greenland determines its fate</a>. Trump's comments have also ushered discussions about the US's broader Arctic strategy, especially as melting ice caps reveal new geopolitical and resource opportunities.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);">Trump views Greenland as a potential American asset, but the chance of the US acquiring Greeland is very low. However, this could raise other issues involving <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bo-3-the-islands-future" target="_blank">the island's future</a>. Greenland’s options include increased autonomy, maintaining ties with Denmark, or pursuing an independent identity. The attention could also boost tourism. A couple of weeks before Trump’s comments, Nuuk recently opened <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-01-2025-bo-4-a-new-airport" target="_blank">a new airport</a> that helps connect visitors to the island.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>